skateboardsusa.com to receive a return authorization\r\n    (RA) number. This RA number is mandatory and should be clearly marked on the package. RA numbers are valid for a\r\n    period of 30 days only. After 30 days, the RA number will automatically delete from our system. Shipping charges are\r\n    not refundable. All exchanges must be shipped via Fed Ex Ground to the address we will provide you with your return\r\n    authorization.</p>\r\n<p>Products returned without an RA from our store will be returned to the owner at the owner\'s expense. Under no\r\n    circumstances is user-damaged product returnable. (i.e. product that has been through water or pressure cracked\r\n    decks that have been overloaded)</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><b>PACKAGING A RETURN</b></p>\r\n<p>When returning merchandise, all items should include all factory packaging and accessories in its original carton\r\n    intact. All merchandise must be shipped via DHL with freight prepaid by the customer with the RA number displayed on\r\n    the outside of the shipping box. For your protection, we recommend you insure your shipment. Please return ONLY\r\n    those products AUTHORIZED for return.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><b>ONLINE SALES AGREEMENT, RELEASE OF LIABILITY &amp; PARENT INFORMATION SALE OF ANY EQUIPMENT ON THIS WEB SITE IS\r\n    EXPRESSLY CONDITIONED ON THE FOLLOWING AGREEMENT. YOU, OR YOUR PARENT/LEGAL GUARDIAN (IF YOU ARE A MINOR), MUST READ\r\n    THIS AGREEMENT PRIOR TO PLACING AN ORDER WITH EVOLVE LONGBOARDS USA LLC.</b></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p>The best safety equipment and the most experienced athlete cannot completely eliminate the risks certain sporting and\r\n    outdoor activities pose. Certain sporting and outdoor activities are inherently dangerous. By purchasing and using\r\n    the equipment sold by Evolve Longboards USA LLC&nbsp;the purchaser understands and voluntarily undertakes the risks\r\n    involved with sporting and outdoor activities, including but are not limited to: electric skateboarding and\r\n    skateboarding. Such risks and dangers include, but are not limited to: sprains, broken bones, bruises, cuts,\r\n    temporary or permanent paralysis and even death. Other risks include: unforeseen weather conditions, hazardous and\r\n    unknown terrain, geographical conditions, failure to properly maintain equipment, failure to obey traffic\r\n    instructions or local laws and engaging in sporting and outdoor activities while physically exhausted or disabled.\r\n    This electric skateboard is a high performance machine and should not used or operated in any way by children under\r\n    the age of 14 years old.&nbsp;<b></b><em>YOU MUST WEAR APPROPRIATE SAFETY EQUIPMENT&nbsp;(ESPECIALLY A HELMET)\r\n        WHENEVER RIDING AN ELECTRIC SKATEBOARD.</em></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p>It is important to use merchandise sold by Evolve&nbsp;Longboards USA LLC&nbsp;in accordance with the manufacturer\'s\r\n    design and recommendations to minimize these risks. However, accidents and unforeseen hazards do exist and the\r\n    purchaser and users of the merchandise sold by Evolve&nbsp;Longboards USA LLC&nbsp;agree as follows:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n    <li>I, the purchaser or user of the merchandise, agree to release Evolve&nbsp;Longboards USA LLC, its owners, agents\r\n        and employees, from any and all liability for damage, injury, paralysis and death to myself, any other person,\r\n        or property, resulting from the use or misuse of the merchandise sold by Evolve&nbsp;Longboards USA LLC.\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>I, the parent of a minor child, agree to release Evolve&nbsp;Longboards USA LLC its owners, agents and\r\n        employees, from any and all liability for damage, injury, paralysis and death to my child, any other person, or\r\n        property, resulting from the use or misuse of the merchandise sold by Evolve&nbsp;Longboards USA LLC.\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>It is agreed that any and all liability of Evolve&nbsp;Longboards USA LLC its owners, agents and employees shall\r\n        be limited to the purchase price of the merchandise.\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>It is agreed that any legal action brought against Evolve&nbsp;Longboards USA LLC&nbsp;for any reason will be\r\n        brought in the state of Michigan.\r\n    </li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>I have read and understand the terms of this agreement. I understand that my purchase and use of the merchandise sold\r\n    by Evolve Longboards USA ads manifests my agreement to the terms of this Agreement. I understand that this Agreement\r\n    releases Evolve Skateboards from any and all claims of liability brought by myself, my minor children, and any other\r\n    third party who uses the merchandise purchased from Evolve Longboards USA.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><b>PLEASE READ THE FOLLOWING TERMS OF USE CAREFULLY BEFORE USING THIS WEBSITE</b>.</p>\r\n<p>All users of this site agree that access to and use of this site are subject to the following terms and conditions\r\n    and other applicable law. If you do not agree to these terms and conditions, please do not use this website.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><b>COPYRIGHT</b></p>\r\n<p>The Evolve&nbsp;Skateboard&nbsp;is a unique design that is protected by design registration and patent pending. The\r\n    entire content included in this site, including but not limited to text, graphics or product is copyrighted as a\r\n    collective work under the Australian and other copyright laws, and is the property of Evolve Skateboards. Permission\r\n    is granted to electronically copy and print hard copy portions of this site for the sole purpose of placing an order\r\n    with Evolve Skateboards or purchasing Evolve&nbsp;Longboards USA LLC&nbsp;products.&nbsp;Any other use, including\r\n    but not limited to the reproduction, distribution, display or transmission of the content of this site is strictly\r\n    prohibited, unless authorized by Evolve&nbsp;Skateboards. You further agree not to change or delete any proprietary\r\n    notices from materials downloaded from the site.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><b>TYPOGRAPHICAL ERRORS</b></p>\r\n<p>In the event that an Evolve&nbsp;Longboards USA LLC&nbsp;product is mistakenly listed at an incorrect price, Evolve\r\n    Longboards LLC reserves the right to refuse or cancel any orders placed for product listed at the incorrect price.\r\n    Evolve Skateboards reserves the right to refuse or cancel any such orders whether or not the order has been\r\n    confirmed and your credit card charged. If your credit card has already been charged for the purchase and your order\r\n    is cancelled, Evolve Longboards USA shall issue a credit to your credit card account in the amount of the incorrect\r\n    price.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><b>PRODUCT AND PRICING INFORMATION</b></p>\r\n<p>Although Evolve&nbsp;Longboards USA LLC&nbsp;has made every effort to display the products and their colors as\r\n    accurately as possible, the displayed colors of the products will depend upon the monitor of the user and Evolve\r\n    Longboards LLC cannot guarantee that the user\'s monitor will accurately portray the actual colors of the products.\r\n    Products displayed may be out-of-stock or discontinued, and prices are subject to change. Purchases may be subject\r\n    to applicable taxes (duties, VAT etc) in the purchaser’s shipping destination. These are to be paid by the purchaser\r\n    and are not included in the shipping cost applied at Evolve Skateboards’ online checkout.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><b>GOVERNING LAW</b></p>\r\n<p>The contract of sale shall be construed in accordance with the law of the United States of America and the State of\r\n    Michigan.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><b>PRIVACY POLICY</b></p>\r\n<p>This privacy policy sets out how Evolve&nbsp;Longboards USA LLC&nbsp;uses and protects any information that you give\r\n    Evolve Skateboards when you use this website.</p>\r\n<p>Evolve Longboards USA LLC is committed to ensuring that your privacy is protected. Should we ask you to provide\r\n    certain information by which you can be identified when using this website, then you can be assured that it will\r\n    only be used in accordance with this privacy statement.</p>\r\n<p>Evolve Longboards USA LLC&nbsp;may change this policy from time to time by updating this page. You should check this\r\n    page from time to time to ensure that you are happy with any changes. This policy is effective from March 19,\r\n    2012</p>\r\n<p><b>WHAT WE COLLECT</b></p>\r\n<p>We may collect the following information:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Name</li>\r\n    <li>Contact information including email address</li>\r\n    <li>Demographic information such as postcode,</li>\r\n    <li>Other information relevant to customer surveys and/or offers</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><b>WHAT WE DO WITH THE INFORMATION WE GATHER</b></p>\r\n<p>We require this information to understand your needs and provide you with a better service, and in particular for the\r\n    following reasons:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Dispatching orders.</li>\r\n    <li>Internal record keeping.</li>\r\n    <li>We may use the information to improve our products and services.</li>\r\n    <li>We may periodically send promotional emails about new products, special offers or other information which we\r\n        think you may find interesting using the email address which you have provided.\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><b>SECURITY</b></p>\r\n<p>We are committed to ensuring that your information is secure. In order to prevent unauthorized access or disclosure,\r\n    we have put in place suitable physical, electronic and managerial procedures to safeguard and secure the information\r\n    we collect online.</p>\r\n<p>How we use cookies</p>\r\n<p>A cookie is a small file which asks permission to be placed on your computer\'s hard drive. Once you agree, the file\r\n    is added and the cookie helps analyse web traffic or lets you know when you visit a particular site. Cookies allow\r\n    web applications to respond to you as an individual. The web application can tailor its operations to your needs,\r\n    likes and dislikes by gathering and remembering information about your preferences.</p>\r\n<p>We use traffic log cookies to identify which pages are being used. This helps us analyse data about webpage traffic\r\n    and improve our website in order to tailor it to customer needs. We only use this information for statistical\r\n    analysis purposes and then the data is removed from the system.</p>\r\n<p>Overall, cookies help us provide you with a better website by enabling us to monitor which pages you find useful and\r\n    which you do not. A cookie in no way gives us access to your computer or any information about you, other than the\r\n    data you choose to share with us.</p>\r\n<p>You can choose to accept or decline cookies. Most web browsers automatically accept cookies, but you can usually\r\n    modify your browser setting to decline cookies if you prefer. This may prevent you from taking full advantage of the\r\n    website.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><b>LINKS TO OTHER WEBSITES</b></p>\r\n<p>Our website may contain links to other websites of interest. However, once you have used these links to leave our\r\n    site, you should note that we do not have any control over that other website. Therefore, we cannot be responsible\r\n    for the protection and privacy of any information which you provide whilst visiting such sites and such sites are\r\n    not governed by this privacy statement. You should exercise caution and look at the privacy statement applicable to\r\n    the website in question.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><b>CONTROLLING YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION</b></p>\r\n<p>We will not sell, distribute or lease your personal information to third parties unless we have your permission or\r\n    are required by law to do so.</p>\r\n<p>You may request details of personal information which we hold about you under the Data Protection Act 1998. A small\r\n    fee will be payable. If you would like a copy of the information held on you please <a\r\n            href=\"http://evolveskateboardsusa.com/pages/contact-us\"> write to us.</a></p>\r\n<p>If you believe that any information we are holding on you is incorrect or incomplete, please write to or email us as\r\n    soon as possible at the above address. We will promptly correct any information found to be incorrect.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><b>QUESTIONS OR CONCERNS</b></p>\r\n<p> If you have any question or concerns in regard to our privacy policy please contact us at\r\n    info@evolveskateboards.usa</p>\r\n',1,'','','','',NULL,'2014-09-23 14:55:43'),(5,'shipping','Оплата и доставка','<h1>Варианты оплаты:</h1>\r\n\r\n<h3>1. Наложенный платеж</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>Преимущества и недостатки:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>+ Вы оплачиваете товар в момент его получения.</strong><br />\r\n<strong>+ Вам не нужно ходить в банк для оплаты заказа или иметь кредитную или дебетовую карту VISA или Mastercard.</strong><br />\r\n<strong>- EMS Почта России возьмет с вас комиссию за перевод денег в наш адрес. Комиссия расчитывается следующим образом:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&middot; при наложенном платеже до 1&nbsp;000 руб. включительно за перевод денег с Вас возьмут 25 руб. + 5% от пересылаемой суммы; (при заказе на 999 р. - 75 р.)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&middot; при наложенном платеже от 1&nbsp;000 до 5&nbsp;000 руб. включительно за перевод денег с Вас возьмут 75 руб. + 4% от суммы, превышающей 1&nbsp;000 руб.; (при заказе 4999 р. - 235 р.)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&middot; при наложенном платеже от 5&nbsp;000 до 20&nbsp;000 руб. включительно за перевод денег с Вас возьмут 235 руб. + 2% от суммы, превышающей 5&nbsp;000 руб. (при заказе 19999 р. - 535 р.)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&middot; при наложенном платеже от 20 000 до 50&nbsp;000 руб. включительно за перевод денег с Вас возьмут 535 руб. + 1% от суммы, превышающей 20 000 руб. (при заказе 49999 р. - 835 р.)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- согласно правилам &laquo;Почты РФ&raquo;: &laquo;&hellip; наложенный платеж не может быть больше объявленной ценности&raquo;, т.е.&nbsp;<strong>не получится сэкономить</strong>&nbsp;на комиссиях.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>В ряде регионов действуют индивидуальные расценки. С подробным описанием услуги &quot;Наложенный платеж EMS Почта России&quot; вы можете ознакомиться по ссылке:<br />\r\n<a href=\"http://www.emspost.ru/platej.php\">http://www.emspost.ru/platej.php</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. Банковские карты Visa, Mastercard и др.</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Особенности:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>+ Мгновенное резервирование товара сразу же после оплаты.</strong><br />\r\n<strong>+ Отсутствие дополнительных комиссий.</strong><br />\r\n<strong>+ Возврат денежных средств, частичная отмена заказа производятся сразу же на вашу карту.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>+ Проведение платежей по банковским картам мы осуществляем напрямую, в партнерстве с банком &quot;ВУЗ-банк&quot;, что гарантирует клиентам высочайшую безопасность.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>При осуществлении платежа по банковской карте вы будете перенаправлены на страницу банка для введения необходимых платежных данных. После проведения платежа вы будете перемещены обратно на страницу магазина и ваш заказ перейдет в статус &quot;Оплачен&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Безопасность онлайн платежей:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Предоставляемая Вами персональная информация (имя, адрес, телефон, e-mail, номер кредитной карты) является конфиденциальной и не подлежит разглашению.&nbsp;Данные Вашей кредитной карты передаются только в зашифрованном виде и не сохраняются на нашем Web-сервере.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Безопасность обработки Интернет-платежей гарантирует ОАО &laquo;ВУЗ-банк&raquo;. Все операции с платежными картами происходят в соответствии с требованиями платежных систем VISA International, MasterCard. При передаче информации используются специальные технологии безопасности карточных онлайн-платежей, обработка данных ведется на безопасном высокотехнологичном сервере процессинговой компании. В случаи использования регулярных платежей, при совершении первой операции номер Вашей карты и срок действия будут сохранены на стороне Банка в безопасном хранилище. По факту выполнения или оказания услуг со стороны компании, данные будут удалены автоматически. Все ресурсы Банка соответствуют стандартам безопасности PCI DSS.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>При проведении операции, Вы будете дополнительно перенаправлены на страницу Банка-Эмитента для ввода подтверждающего кода безопасности (в случае если банк, выпустивший Вашу карту, поддерживает технологию 3DSecure, и Ваша карта также поддерживает данную программу).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3D Secure &ndash; процедура дополнительной аутентификации держателя карты, предназначенная для обеспечения гарантированной безопасности платежей по банковским картам в Сети Интернет.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Технологическое решение 3D Secure имеет свой собственный бренд в каждой из платежных систем:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- Verified by Visa &ndash; по картам платежной системы Visa Int.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- MasterCard Secure Code &ndash; по картам, выпущенным в рамках MasterCard Int</p>\r\n\r\n<p>В независимости от названия, технология 3D Secure предполагает защищенную сессию при проведении интернет-транзакции и позволяет пользователям-держателям карты, подтвердить правомерность операции для Банка выпустивший карту.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>В случае возникновения вопросов по поводу данной конфиденциальности предоставляемой Вами информации, Вы можете связаться с ОАО &laquo;ВУЗ-банк&raquo; по телефону: 8 (343) 378-78-78.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Обработка и отгрузка товаров осуществляется по будням с 11-00 до 20-00 (GMT+5 - Екатеринбург, +2 часа от Москвы).</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h1>ДОСТАВКА</h1>\r\n\r\n<h3>Варианты доставки:</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>1. Бесплатно</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Заказы на сумму свыше <strong>3 000 рублей в любую точку России доставляются бесплатно!</strong> Доставка заказа возможна до пункта выдачи (не во всех городах) или до двери вашего дома или офиса (в небольших населенных пунктах возможна доставка до почтового отделения).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>При выборе способа оплаты &quot;Наложенный платеж&quot; вам придется оплатить комиссию Почты России за пересылку денежных средств. Подробнее об этом читайте в разделе &quot;Оплата&quot;.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. Самовывоз</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Не хотите заказывать доставку? Вначале хотите попробовать? Планируете быть в Екатеринбурге или Перми?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Вы можете заказать товар и заехать за ним в удобное время. Оплатить товар можно заранее или в магазине.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3. </strong><a href=\"http://www.emspost.ru\"><strong>EMS Почта России</strong></a><br />\r\nДоставка &quot;до дверей&quot;, в некоторых небольших городах - &quot;до почтового отделения&quot;. Стоимость доставки будет рассчитана в процессе оформления заказа.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>В некоторых случаях мы можем воспользоваться другим методом доставки. Для согласования альтернативного способа доставки наш оператор свяжется с вами по телефону, указанному при оформлении заказа.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Новое правило EMS:</strong>&nbsp;<strong>При получении посылки нужно обязательно иметь при себе паспорт!</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4. </strong><strong><a href=\"http://www.im-logistics.ru\">IM&nbsp;Logistics</a></strong><br />\r\nВозможна доставка до дверей или пунктов выдачи!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Зачастую работают быстрее EMS и Почты России! Срок доставки - от 5 до 13 дней!&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Список городов, в которые возможна доставка:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Москва</li>\r\n	<li>Санкт-Петербург</li>\r\n	<li>Екатеринбург</li>\r\n	<li>Брянск</li>\r\n	<li>Владимир</li>\r\n	<li>Вологда</li>\r\n	<li>Иваново</li>\r\n	<li>Калуга</li>\r\n	<li>Кострома</li>\r\n	<li>Нижний Новгород</li>\r\n	<li>Орел</li>\r\n	<li>Рязань</li>\r\n	<li>Тула</li>\r\n	<li>Тверь</li>\r\n	<li>Тюмень</li>\r\n	<li>Челябинск</li>\r\n	<li>Ярославль</li>\r\n	<li>Ростов-На-Дону</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>5. Международная доставка</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Мы не отправляем товары за рубеж.</p>\r\n',1,'','','','',NULL,'2014-09-23 14:57:59'),(6,'contact-us','Contact us','<p>ООО &laquo;ИВОЛВ РУС&raquo; ИНН 6671468126 ОГРН 1146671028063<br />\r\nТелефон/факс: 8-800-500-12-46 (бесплатно)<br />\r\nг. Екатеринбург, ул. Куйбышева 55 - 509<br />\r\ne-mail для связи: <a href=\"mailto:info@evolveskateboards.ru\">info@evolveskateboards.ru</a></p>\r\n',1,'','','','',NULL,'2014-09-23 14:59:19'),(7,'videos','Видео','<p>Sunday Burn</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Time lapse snubnose assembly</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Carpark Madness 3</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pumping the Evolve &#39;super carve&#39; truck to gain speed without using the motor.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We&#39;ve had a lot of interest from people wondering which top shelf wheels are compatible with our boards. Here&#39;s a little vid that lists them while showing them in action.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Testing out the Metro Express slide wheels (the no music version for viewers in Germany).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Using Abec 11 fly wheels 76mm 75a but you can also use the 83mm fly wheels, great feature of the Evolve boards - interchangeable with quality gear like this. I was also testing the battery performance, it went for 32km&#39;s, 1 charge. It takes 4 hrs to recharge once fully flat. I purposely ran it flat to show how it can be kicked pushed home if necessary. Super fun!!!!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Battery Test - The result was 29.36km&#39;s in about 2 hours. There was a really strong breeze and all different types on terrain and I weigh 82kg&#39;s. If there was no breeze it probably would of done 35km&#39;s. Started at Nobbies Beach, rode all the way to Seaworld, then rode all the way back to Hedges Ave, then did the Broady footpath 5 times up and back. I couldn&#39;t fit it all into this video as it would have taken 8 minutes at 2000% speed up. The battery indicator light came on the remote and then i had about another 40mins of riding time. Basically.....I was stoked when the battery went flat, my legs and toes were really sore!! Also had a camera malfunctioned and came unstuck on the bottom of my board a few times, sorry for the marks on the screen at the end of the vid! Rad tune - Parachute Youth &#39;can&#39;t get better than this&#39;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Evolve Skateboards late arvo fun! Here&#39;s the pintail with Abec 11 fly wheels 75a 83mm....awesomeness! This board is ultra light, fast and smooth....what more could you want in an electric longboard with the super carve trucks!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This hill was steep and about 200m long, really made the motor work in this one!!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Noise testing the board.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Roll testing the board with the electrics turned off.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Fiik 800 watt Street surfer vs Evolve 200 watt pintail - race off! The 2 boards are very different as this Fiik board is designed for all terrain and concrete surfaces and the evolve is designed for concrete surfaces. The differences in weight and materials result in the Evolve board being a lot faster, quieter and smoother. The Fiik board is still great fun and a very different product.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Part 1 - About the Evolve brand and things to consider when buying an electric skateboard.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A detailed look at our electric pintail board. &nbsp;Sorry for the length of these videos!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n',1,'information','','','',NULL,'2014-09-23 15:06:12'),(8,'troubleshooting','Troubleshooting','<h2>BAMBOO SERIES</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Signal lights on hand remote:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>red light solid = battery in board getting low.</li>\r\n	<li>red light flickering = battery in remote needs to be changed.</li>\r\n	<li>green light is flashing &nbsp;= remote needs to be paired with board. &nbsp;To pair the remote with your board press the reverse button once.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Signal lights on battery box:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>8 flashes = low power in battery</li>\r\n	<li>4 or 7 flashes = controller problem. See our&nbsp;<a href=\"https://vimeo.com/60523260\" target=\"_blank\">drive wheel is not spinning video</a>&nbsp;and if the problem persists contact us at info@evolveskateboardsusa.com</li>\r\n	<li>3 flashes (must pull trigger firstly then wait two seconds for it to flash quickly) = motor or controller connection problem. See our&nbsp;<a href=\"https://vimeo.com/60523260\" target=\"_blank\">drive wheel is not spinning video</a>&nbsp;and if the problem persists contact us at info@evolveskateboardsusa.com</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>My board has completely stopped and the drive wheel is not spinning or seems stuck - please check each of the following steps</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Is the lamp on the battery flashing 8 times? &nbsp;If so the battery is flat and the board needs to be charged.</li>\r\n	<li>Is the battery indicator light on the remote flickering red? &nbsp;If so replace the batteries.</li>\r\n	<li>Is the green light flashing on the remote? &nbsp;If so it needs to be paired with the board by pressing the reverse button once.</li>\r\n	<li>Is the green light on the remote off? &nbsp;If so there may be a connection problem. Please refer to our&nbsp;<a href=\"https://vimeo.com/60527400\">connection video</a>&nbsp;for further instruction on how to fix the issue.</li>\r\n	<li>If the problem still persists see our&nbsp;<a href=\"https://vimeo.com/60523260\" target=\"_blank\">drive wheel is not spinning video</a>&nbsp;and if that doesn&#39;t get you back up and running contact us at info@evolveskateboardsusa.com&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>My board is dropping in and out of connection/The power is cutting in and out - please check each of the following steps</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Make sure your hand is always gripping the remote while riding.</li>\r\n	<li>Make sure you are not covering the top of the remote while riding as this can interfere with the reception.</li>\r\n	<li>Make sure the board and remote batteries are not low.</li>\r\n	<li>If the problem still persists please refer to our&nbsp;<a href=\"https://vimeo.com/60527400\" target=\"_blank\">connection video</a>&nbsp;for further instruction on how to fix the issue.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>My board is not charging/There is a green light on the charger but it should be red.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Check that the plug and charging point from the charger are inserted fully and correctly.</li>\r\n	<li>While the charger is plugged in try wiggling the charging point in the battery box slightly to see if the red light comes on.</li>\r\n	<li>Check to see if the charger fuse in the battery box has blown. &nbsp;Please follow&nbsp;<a href=\"https://vimeo.com/60542335\" target=\"_blank\">this video.</a></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The green light is flashing on my remote and the board is not working.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>This means that the remote has lost pairing with your board. &nbsp;Press the reverse button once to pair the board with the remote.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>CARBON SERIES</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>My board has completely stopped and the drive wheel is not spinning or seems stuck - please check each of the following steps</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Is the lamp on the battery flashing 8 times? &nbsp;If so the battery is flat and the board needs to be charged.</li>\r\n	<li>Is the battery indicator light on the remote flickering red? &nbsp;If so replace the batteries.</li>\r\n	<li>Is the green light flashing on the remote? &nbsp;If so it needs to be paired with the board by pressing the reverse button once.</li>\r\n	<li>Is the green light on the remote off? &nbsp;If so there may be a connection problem. Please refer to our&nbsp;<a href=\"https://vimeo.com/83481297\" target=\"_blank\">connection video</a>&nbsp;for further instruction on how to fix the issue.</li>\r\n	<li>If the problem still persists see our&nbsp;<a href=\"https://vimeo.com/83484189\" target=\"_blank\">battery case and connections video</a>&nbsp;and if that doesn&#39;t get you back up and running contact us at info@evolveskateboardsusa.com</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>My board is dropping in and out of connection/The power is cutting in and out - please check each of the following steps</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Make sure your hand is always gripping the remote while riding.</li>\r\n	<li>Make sure you are not covering the top of the remote while riding as this can interfere with the reception.</li>\r\n	<li>Make sure the board and remote batteries are not low.</li>\r\n	<li>If the problem still persists please refer to our&nbsp;<a href=\"https://vimeo.com/83481297\" target=\"_blank\">connection video</a>&nbsp;for further instruction on how to fix the issue.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>My board is not charging/There is a green light on the charger but it should be red.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Check that the plug and charging point from the charger are inserted fully and correctly.</li>\r\n	<li>While the charger is plugged in try wiggling the charging point in the battery box slightly to see if the red light comes on.</li>\r\n	<li>Check to see if the charger fuse in the battery box has blown. &nbsp;Please follow&nbsp;<a href=\"https://vimeo.com/83484189\" target=\"_blank\">this video.</a></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The green light is flashing on my remote and the board is not working.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>This means that the remote has lost pairing with your board. &nbsp;Press the reverse button once to pair the board with the remote.</li>\r\n	<li>If the remote is still not paired please see our&nbsp;<a href=\"https://vimeo.com/83481297\" target=\"_blank\">connection video.</a></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>View our online manual here:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Follow the link below.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>http://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0150/5168/files/Evolve-User-Manual.pdf?1779</p>\r\n',1,'information','','','',NULL,'2014-09-23 17:08:34'),(9,'information','Информация','<p><a href=\"http://evolveskateboardsusa.com/pages/videos\">Evolve Videos</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://evolveskateboardsusa.com/blogs/news\">News</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://evolveskateboardsusa.com/pages/testimonials\">Customer Testimonials</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://evolveskateboardsusa.com/pages/shipping\">Shipping &amp; Transit Times</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://evolveskateboardsusa.com/pages/frequently-asked-questions\">Frequently Asked Questions</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://evolveskateboardsusa.com/pages/rider-tips-maintenance\">Rider Tips &amp; Maintenance Suggestions</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://evolveskateboardsusa.com/pages/troubleshooting\">Troubleshooting Issues</a></p>\r\n',1,'','','','',NULL,'2014-09-23 18:58:20'),(10,'testimonials','Testimonials','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>My first week of owning my snubnose review:</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span><span>Previously, I only carved with Loaded boards (vanguards) flex #2 &amp; #3, but the&nbsp;</span>Snubnose has retired everyone of my Loaded boards.&nbsp;</span><span>I have never surfed on water or snow, so I cannot compare, b</span><span>ut I have surfed the best of smooth black asphalt a</span><span>nd the Snubnose just plan Destroys (melts) asphalt. The&nbsp;</span><span>Snubnose can carve like no other board I\'ve surfed on!&nbsp;</span><span>With 18 miles boarding distance and the greatest carver out on the market,&nbsp;</span><span>Evolve is way more advanced then the 6 mile board that might come out someday.</span>\r\n</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">I\'ve learned to propel up to 26 mph on level ground!<br><span>1st pic shows 22.4 mph &amp; distance 18.4 miles (awesome!)<br>2nd pic shows 29.6 mph &amp; distance 9.3 (another 9 miles to go).</span>\r\n</p>\r\n<img src=\"//cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0232/5683/files/snubnose_review_medium.jpg?1103\"> <img\r\n        src=\"//cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0232/5683/files/snubnose_review_2_medium.jpg?1102\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span></span><span>Love the Snubnose boys!</span><span>I Received my Snubnose for my 60th birthday from my wife!&nbsp;</span><span>\"Stay young and learn to play\"</span><br><br><span>Robert from Colorado</span>\r\n</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</span>\r\n</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Evolve USA</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Just got my board this morning and charged it to full for my first sesh.&nbsp; Fast forward about 2 hrs and\r\n    the smile on my face has been permanently fixed since the first 100yds on the board.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.2;\">I road on bike paths for the most of my day but once I found an abandoned parking lot, it was epic. Opening up the board while carving up the smooth surface felt like being out in the ocean on a glassy day with the entire break to myself. That zen like feeling, or in Hawaii we call it \"pono\" (harmonious) feeling came back when it was just me and that open space feeling the board, sun, and wind!</span>\r\n</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">I\'m currently charging her back up for another session in a few hours and I want my legs to feel spanked by&nbsp;<span\r\n        class=\"aBn\" tabindex=\"0\" data-term=\"goog_704006906\"><span class=\"aQJ\">tomorrow</span></span>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">So thanks again Bruce, I\'ll be looking to place an order on the AT soon...</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Warm regards,</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Walt, CALIFORNIA</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">\r\n    -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\r\n<p><span>Evolve USA</span></p>\r\n<p><span>What a great day to ride in NY, this board is so much fun,worth every penny, you can go anywhere in NY and I love the looks when people see me not using my feet,these cyclist guys vid me on their Go Cam on their handlebars while I was cruising in front of them,very cool...will try to post vid to you</span>Hi\r\n    Jeff,</p>\r\n<p>Your board is exactly what I wanted for so long.&nbsp;I dreamed of a board which is still&nbsp;longboard, a small\r\n    motor which give you enough power for carving. I&nbsp;don\'t need a hill-climber, because I don\'t use the board for&nbsp;transportation\r\n    (moving from A to B). The most important thing is to&nbsp;keep the board light and close to the Longboard specs. For\r\n    my taste,&nbsp;the battery capacity could be even smaller to save weight.&nbsp;Your board, is not a e-board. Its a\r\n    longboard which has a small motor&nbsp;to carve. That it!</p>\r\n<p>Mike, NY</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    .........................................................................................................................................................................................................................</p>\r\n<p>Hi Jeff,</p>\r\n<p>I\'d like to tell you again, the trucks are amazing. Had a session in&nbsp;the morning, and I pushed so hard around\r\n    the corner. The wheels are&nbsp;glued on the asphalt and the gravity kicks you so hard in the board.&nbsp;Its like\r\n    snowboarding ( I guess surfing too, but never tried it).&nbsp;My metroboard was boring compared to your board. The\r\n    key are the&nbsp;trucks...</p>\r\n<p>Keep goin!</p>\r\n<p>Anon, Germany</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    .........................................................................................................................................................................................................................</p>\r\n<p>Hi Jeff/Fleur,</p>\r\n<p>I am just back from an early 10km ride to get some croissants and baguette for the family and I wanted to provide you\r\n    a feedback on the board I received on Monday.</p>\r\n<p>This is the best device I have been riding ever! It is worth every penny! I am used to skiing, mono-skiing,\r\n    snow-boarding, roller-skating and the evolve board is ahead of all this. In fact it is perfectly filling the gap\r\n    between two winter seasons.</p>\r\n<p>I found the quality of the board amazing: optimized for speed, range, quality of the board (bamboo), the nice plate\r\n    with the number of the board... Love it all.</p>\r\n<p>Congrats.</p>\r\n<p>David, Switzerland</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    .........................................................................................................................................................................................................................</p>\r\n<p>Thanx heaps n the boards are so so much fun. Best investment ever</p>\r\n<p>Michael, WA Australia</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    .........................................................................................................................................................................................................................</p>\r\n<p>Hey Jeff,</p>\r\n<p>The Pintail is awesome! The trucks are amazingly smooth, the board coasts along with very little resistance, and the\r\n    hand controller has a great feel to it and smooth throttle and brake&nbsp;response!</p>\r\n<p>Jake, VIC Australia</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    .........................................................................................................................................................................................................................</p>\r\n<p>VIA FACEBOOK:</p>\r\n<p>I found the solution to the Olympics congestion in London: commuting with the Evolve board: faster, cheaper and 1000x\r\n    more fun!</p>\r\n<p>Phillipe, UK</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    .........................................................................................................................................................................................................................</p>\r\n<p>Jeff you said \" you\'ve got to get into the carving \" and o boy I ave. can\'t do your 180\'s yet. But I\'ve got the back\r\n    wheels of me pintail BARKING</p>\r\n<p>Mark, UK</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    .........................................................................................................................................................................................................................</p>\r\n<p>This board is off the charts!! Still sooooo amped on it!!</p>\r\n<p>Dylan, Australia</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    .........................................................................................................................................................................................................................</p>\r\n<p>if these things could spit fire they still would not be any cooler to ride</p>\r\n<p>Mark, UK</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    .........................................................................................................................................................................................................................</p>\r\n<p>Customer service A+++  Thanks team!</p>\r\n<p>Mark, Australia</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    .........................................................................................................................................................................................................................</p>\r\n<p>Beats eglide in so many ways..</p>\r\n<p>Kim, Norway</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    .........................................................................................................................................................................................................................</p>\r\n<p>just had the best ride of my life! drove on freshly laid asphalt along the water, while the sun set over the\r\n    water.</p>\r\n<p>Bjorn, Sweden</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    .........................................................................................................................................................................................................................</p>\r\n<p>THIS IS SERIOUSLY THE BEST THING I HAVE EVER BOUGHT!!!!</p>\r\n<p>Troy, Australia</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    .........................................................................................................................................................................................................................</p>\r\n<p>SO FAST! oooooohh shiitttt! i need to get used to this compared to my older ElektroSkate 500W Air. feels so much\r\n    stronger too...i hit a few speed bumps at my apartment and already got dirt and scratches on it. yeeee! but I feel\r\n    like I will be taking a better care of my new baby than any other boards i have....and i have a lot xD lol. Thank\r\n    you! VIDEO coming soon....</p>\r\n<p>Yuriy, US</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    .........................................................................................................................................................................................................................</p>\r\n<p>Just did a short ride in Hyde Park before the rain caught me. It is awesome: really feels like a skateboard and with\r\n    the loose trucks, the carves are amazing. I had a hard time believing the 200W motor could go as fast as a 600W but\r\n    it does! It goes as fast as my previous 600W board but is much lighter and much more maneuverable. Best electric\r\n    board on the market for sure! I also like the easy switch high/ low speed. Now I just need some sun...does Evolve\r\n    ship Australian sun as well?</p>\r\n<p>Philippe, UK</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    .........................................................................................................................................................................................................................</p>\r\n<p>God made Jeff so we could have this awesome carving machine legs stuffed after hard 1 hour 4 min ride can\'t wait for\r\n    legs to get fitter for longer ride and the battery doesn\'t even look like slowing any time soon cheers Jeff.</p>\r\n<p>Wayne, Australia</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    .........................................................................................................................................................................................................................</p>\r\n<p>‎2 1/2 hrs later = sore legs, toes and back - sore face too, haven\'t smiled so much for so long b4 with my clothes on\r\n    !</p>\r\n<p>Darren, Australia</p>\r\n<span>-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</span>\r\n<span>&nbsp;</span><span>I\'ve learned to propel up to 26 mph on level ground!</span>\r\n',1,'','','','',NULL,'2014-09-23 19:12:29'),(11,'rider-tips-maintenance','Rider Tips & Maintenance','<p>How to get the best performance out of your battery - Bamboo and Carbon&nbsp;Series</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are two main factors that will get you the best battery life:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. There is a sweet spot on the board for best efficiency.&nbsp; To achieve the maximum range out of your battery its best to ride in full speed mode on the remote and only accelerate to 30-50% and hold this speed.&nbsp; This will still allow the board to travel fast (15.5 mph) without putting a large current through the electrical setup.&nbsp; To slow down you can then just go to neutral mode on the remote and carve to control speed and only use the brake function if really needed.&nbsp; Maintaining a speed is the best way to achieve the biggest range during your session.&nbsp; If you use the trigger in a heavy motion such as pulling all the way in just to get up to a medium speed and constantly using the brake function this will reduce battery life.&nbsp; Also if you use &#39;slow speed mode&#39; and pull the trigger all the way in this uses the same amount of current as the &#39;full speed mode&#39; and will drain the battery faster (refer to your manual on how to switch between modes).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Board maintenance is crucial to good battery life. In particular check that&nbsp;bearings are clean and rolling freely and if your wheels are getting warn rotate or replace them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How to clean/change the wheel bearings and rotate wheels - Bamboo and Carbon series</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://vimeo.com/60543916\" target=\"_blank\">Please see our video for explanation</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How to keep your board riding quiet and general maintenance tips &ndash; Bamboo and Carbon series</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Check your bearings every 4 weeks to see if they are spinning freely and quiet including the drive gear/wheel.&nbsp; Check all screws are tight (not too tight) throughout the board (wheel nuts, motor bracket, belt cover etc).&nbsp; Rotate all your wheels every so often so the wear is even over the whole board.&nbsp; Always keep the battery near full charge.&nbsp; Clean all parts (except the deck) with a damp cloth then wipe with a dry cloth.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For maintenance guidelines for the Carbon Street board please see<a href=\"https://vimeo.com/83488093\" target=\"_blank\">&nbsp;this video</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For maintenance guidelines for the Carbon AT board please see&nbsp;<a href=\"https://vimeo.com/83540503\" target=\"_blank\">this video</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Best Terrain for the Evolve boards and what to avoid &ndash; Bamboo series and Carbon Street&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The best surfaces to ride the boards on are roads/footpaths with a decent surface.&nbsp; Roads that are quite rough with loose rocks or gravel and footpaths with large expansion joints will obviously feel much rougher under foot.&nbsp; The Evolve boards are really a longboard with a motor attached so any surface you would ride a longboard on the Evolve can also be ridden.&nbsp; Also, be watchful of changes in level or small lips that may cause the motor and bracket to be scraped.&nbsp;&nbsp; Always be in search for the perfect spot to ride, just like when you search for the perfect wave and snowboard run.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Charging the battery and&nbsp;storage&nbsp;&ndash; Bamboo and Carbon series</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When charging the battery, firstly insert the charger into the battery box, then insert into the mains power in the wall.&nbsp; Try to keep the battery close to full charge when not in use and store in a room temperature environment.&nbsp; Do not store in a hot car or similar.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How to tighten or loosen your drive belt - Bamboo series</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://vimeo.com/61307301\" target=\"_blank&quot;\">Please see our video for explanation.</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How to adjust your drive belt - Carbon series</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://vimeo.com/83490742\" target=\"_blank\">Please see our video for explanation.</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How to clean your bamboo deck</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://vimeo.com/61310474\" target=\"_blank&quot;\">Please see our video for explanation.</a></p>\r\n',1,'','','','',NULL,'2014-09-23 19:14:16'),(12,'compare-evolve-skateboard-models','Compare Evolve Electric Skateboard Models','<table>\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h1>СЕРИЯ BAMBOO</h1>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n			<h1>СЕРИЯ CARBON</h1>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thea